I have a table:
table_name_id :ID
  id
  link
  login_token
  description

I am trying to get the current value of a login token, but I am getting an error.
Imputing the value of 'login_token'
Error:
GET /login_token/login_token.php

How can I get the current value of login_token?

A:

If you are using the loginToken interface you can access the token from the table.
If you are not using the loginToken interface you can access the token from the table.
You can access the token from the table and get the current value.

A:

http://php.net/manual/en/function.renew-inc.php
You can access the value by using the note: "Use this variable to store the value as a string, or make it available from within a function."
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    $('.login_token').on('click',function(e){
        var loginToken = $(this).val();

        if (loginToken==""){
            e.preventDefault();
        }
        else{
            $('.logout').html(loginToken);
        }

        $('.login_token').attr('value', loginToken);
        $('.logout').modal();
    });
});

